{%- comment -%}
  Custom @font-face for Bubba's brand fonts (Allora, Alosta).
  These are licensed display fonts, not available via Shopify's font_picker,
  so they're loaded directly from theme assets instead of settings.font_heading.

  DROP-IN STEP: upload the licensed web font files (woff2 preferred, woff as
  fallback) to this theme's /assets folder named exactly:
    allora.woff2 / allora.woff
    alosta.woff2 / alosta.woff
  via Shopify Admin → Edit code → Assets → Add a new asset (or push via GitHub).
  Nothing else needs to change — the @font-face src below already points here,
  and base.css already references var(--font-allora) / var(--font-alosta).
  Until the files exist, these requests 404 silently and the Raleway fallback
  in the font stack is used instead, so nothing breaks in the meantime.
{%- endcomment -%}

<style>
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Allora';
    src:
      {%- if 'allora.woff2' | asset_url -%}
        url('{{ 'allora.woff2' | asset_url }}') format('woff2'),
      {%- endif -%}
      url('{{ 'allora.woff' | asset_url }}') format('woff');
    font-weight: normal;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
  }

  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Alosta';
    src:
      {%- if 'alosta.woff2' | asset_url -%}
        url('{{ 'alosta.woff2' | asset_url }}') format('woff2'),
      {%- endif -%}
      url('{{ 'alosta.woff' | asset_url }}') format('woff');
    font-weight: normal;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
  }

  :root {
    --font-allora: 'Allora', {{ settings.font_heading.family }}, serif;
    --font-alosta: 'Alosta', {{ settings.font_subheading.family }}, sans-serif;
  }
</style>
